00:00:05.520 --> 00:00:07.890
So let's just review
what a quadrant is.

00:00:07.890 --> 00:00:10.680
A quadrant are each
of the four sections

00:00:10.680 --> 00:00:11.750
of the coordinate plane.

00:00:11.750 --> 00:00:13.250
And when we talk
about the sections,

00:00:13.250 --> 00:00:15.870
we're talking about the sections
as divided by the coordinate

00:00:15.870 --> 00:00:16.960
axes.

00:00:16.960 --> 00:00:20.600
So this right here is the
x-axis and this up-down axis

00:00:20.600 --> 00:00:21.726
is the y-axis.

00:00:21.726 --> 00:00:23.600
And you can see it
divides a coordinate plane

00:00:23.600 --> 00:00:25.140
into four sections.

00:00:25.140 --> 00:00:27.950
We call each of these
sections quadrants.

00:00:27.950 --> 00:00:31.920
This one over here, where both
the x-values and the y-values

00:00:31.920 --> 00:00:34.910
are positive, we call
the first quadrant.

00:00:34.910 --> 00:00:37.980
And we use the Roman numeral I.

00:00:37.980 --> 00:00:40.170
Then if we kind of
move counterclockwise

00:00:40.170 --> 00:00:43.120
around the coordinate
plane, this quadrant where

00:00:43.120 --> 00:00:47.070
the x-values are negative and
the y-values are positive,

00:00:47.070 --> 00:00:48.825
we call this the
second quadrant.

