second quadrant.

00:00:56.050 --> 00:00:59.120
Then we go down here where
both the x-values are negative

00:00:59.120 --> 00:01:00.880
and the y-values are negative.

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:03.110
We call this the third
quadrant, once again

00:01:03.110 --> 00:01:04.660
using Roman numerals.

00:01:04.660 --> 00:01:07.430
Then finally the quadrant
where the x-values are positive

00:01:07.430 --> 00:01:09.180
but the y-values
are negative, we

00:01:09.180 --> 00:01:11.560
